    "body": "I'm having trouble fully tracking this one down. One thing that's worth noting is that the limits go back to being good if you fill out the 2x2 layout. My suspicion at the moment is that it has something to do with the extra, invisible axis that gets created by the `_subplots()` function in `tools/plotting.py` to fill out the 2x2 array.\n\nYou can actually make this particular issue go away by modifying the `_subplots()` function to not create that extra axis, but I don't understand enough about the plotting system to know what kind of effects that would have on other plots.\n\nCode to repro the problem:\n\n``` python\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nnp.random.seed(100)\n\nn_rows = 200\nexample_df = pd.DataFrame({\n    'count1': np.random.exponential(50, n_rows).astype(int),\n    'count2': np.random.exponential(100, n_rows).astype(int),\n    'count3': np.random.exponential(20, n_rows).astype(int),\n    'season': np.random.randint(1, 5, n_rows)\n})\nexample_df['totalcount'] = example_df['count1'] + example_df['count2']\n\n# Sensible Limits\nexample_df.boxplot(['count1', 'count2'], by='season')\nplt.show()\n```\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1460294/3383191/2e0a5ec2-fc47-11e3-82fe-be6b491f0c1c.png)\n\n``` python\n# Bad limits - grid not filled out\nexample_df.boxplot(['count1', 'count2', 'totalcount'], by='season')\nplt.show()\n```\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1460294/3383195/3caea7da-fc47-11e3-8f92-de0aa49043a0.png)\n\n``` python\n# Sensible limits again once you fill the grid\nexample_df.boxplot(['count1', 'count2', 'count3', 'totalcount'], by='season')\nplt.show()\n```\n\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1460294/3383196/46ec6b4c-fc47-11e3-98f9-dac71ad958b9.png)\n"
  },
